  "description": "<p><a href=\"/wiki/Help:Reverting\" title=\"Help:Reverting\">Reverted</a> edits by <a href=\"/wiki/Special:Contributions/203.197.118.89\" title=\"Special:Contributions/203.197.118.89\">203.197.118.89</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/User_talk:203.197.118.89\" title=\"User talk:203.197.118.89\">talk</a>) to last version by KhabarNegar</p>\n<table style=\"background-color: #fff; color: #202122;\" data-mw=\"interface\">\n\t\t\t\t<col class=\"diff-marker\" />\n\t\t\t\t<col class=\"diff-content\" />\n\t\t\t\t<col class=\"diff-marker\" />\n\t\t\t\t<col class=\"diff-content\" />\n\t\t\t\t<tr class=\"diff-title\" lang=\"en\">\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #fff; color: #202122; text-align: center;\">← Previous revision</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #fff; color: #202122; text-align: center;\">Revision as of 12:37, 13 June 2013</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr><tr>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-lineno\">Line 1:</td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-lineno\">Line 1:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>{{Wiktionary}}</div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>{{Wiktionary}}</div></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>'''Bangladeshi''' may refer to:</div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>'''Bangladeshi''' may refer to:</div></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>A person from [[Bangladesh]], or of Bangladeshi descent. For information about the [[Bangladeshi people]], see [[Demographics of Bangladesh]] and [[Culture of Bangladesh]]. </div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"+\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>A person from [[Bangladesh]], or of Bangladeshi descent. For information about the [[Bangladeshi people]], see [[Demographics of Bangladesh]] and [[Culture of Bangladesh]]. <ins style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none;\">For specific [[Bangladeshis]], see [[List of Bangladeshis]].</ins></div></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>BANGLADESHI AND BENGALI:</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>Most people don’t know the difference between Bengali and Bangladeshi identity. They are two different identities. Bangladeshi people are often confused as Bengali. They are quite different. They (Bangladeshi) have separate language with accent, history, culture and geographical demarcation. A Bangladeshi may often claim to be but not exactly a pure Bengali.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>Bengali language is originally based on Calcutta (India) dialect. It is originally spoken in both bank of the Bhagirathi (lower Ganges) river, from the Farakka (Barrage) to the Sundorban (Forest) in southern West Bengal. This part of land is original Bengal from view point of linguistic geography. To be specific, the districts of Howrah, Hoogly, 24 Parganas, Burdwan, Birbhum, Bankura, Nadia, Murshidabad, Jashohar are the land of original Bengal.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>Bangladeshi people do not speak Bengali language. Bangladeshi people speak Bangladeshi language. It is quite different from Bengali language. Bengali and Bangladeshi is like or more than Swish-German difference or Hindi-Punjabi difference. Bengali is considered the official language of Bangladeshi people. Though officially Bengali is considered their mother tongue, virtually they speak Bangladeshi which is far different from being Bengali.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>Bangladeshi people (except Brahmans) cannot be awarded Bengali identity. Brahmans are a race who originally comes from North India. They do not fall into the Bengali-Bangladeshi classification. The Bangladeshi language, accent, intonation, culture is quite different from those of Bengali. Bangladeshi people are known in different names to different neighbouring places. Such as the Bhatia (north Bengal and Assam), Rohinga, (Burma), Banggal (Kolkata), Diku in Jharkhand, etc. They are different from being Bengali.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>Normally the people of Bangladesh claim Bengali as their official mother tongue and official identity. Virtually it is their step-motherly tongue and step-fatherly identity. But due to emotional attachment of 1971 war this fact is unknown to many and kept secret.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>A remarkable fact is that all the great Bengalee personalities came from this part of original Bengal area. They are Raja Rammohan, Keshab Sen, Sabarna Roy Chowdhury, Netaji Subhas, Ishwar Chandra, Bankim Chandra, Sharat Chandra, Rabindra Nath, Madhusudan, Kazi Nazrul, Bibhuti Bhushan, Tara Shankar, Bidhan Roy, etc.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>Those who migrated from east-Pakistan or Bangladesh are originally Bangladeshi. We find Bangladeshi scent / odour in their body and accent. But from second generation onwards they are identified as Neo-Bengali (or Nabya Banggali). And from third generation onwards they can be considered Bengali. Therefore virtually 3 identities exist, the Bengali, Bangladeshi and Neo-Bengali.</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>REFERENCES</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>1. Kanak Chandra Sarkar, \"Banglar Samaj O Sanskriti\" (Bengali), Published by Ratna Prakashan, Kolkata-75. (www.wetpaint.com)</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\" data-marker=\"−\"></td>\n  <td style=\"color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>For specific [[Bangladeshis]], see [[List of Bangladeshis]].</div></td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty diff-side-added\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>* Note that there is no language called \"Bangladeshi\".  See [[Languages of Bangladesh]].</div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>* Note that there is no language called \"Bangladeshi\".  See [[Languages of Bangladesh]].</div></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>* [[Bangladeshi cuisine]]</div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\"></td>\n  <td style=\"background-color: #f8f9fa; color: #202122; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #eaecf0; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><div>* [[Bangladeshi cuisine]]</div></td>\n</tr>\n</table>",
